comments: Rozier (CHA) maintains a rested hand on Beal's (WAS) right arm and removes it before cleanly dislodging the ball away.
Rozier (CHA) gathers the loose ball and takes two steps before elevating for the layup.
Beal (WAS) is jumping in front of Rozier's (CHA) path and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs as Rozier jumps toward Beal during the layup attempt.
Gafford (WAS) turns to roll toward the lane and incidental contact occurs with Martin (CHA) as Martin goes under the pick.
Kuzma (WAS) and Bridges (CHA) engage and disengage with one another as Bridges begins rolling.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) and Martin (CHA) make incidental foot-to-foot contact with one another as Martin jab steps.
Martin (CHA) maintains his left foot as his pivot as he starts his dribble in the corner.
Avdija (WAS) brings his hands forward and marginal contact occurs with Ball's (CHA) front as Ball changes direction at the end of the drive.
Gafford (WAS) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
After they come together in the lane, Martin (CHA) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Caldwell-Pope (WAS) before any incidental contact occurs during rebounding.
Bridges (CHA) jumps towards Caldwell-Pope (WAS) and marginal contact occurs after Caldwell-Pope has saved the ball.
Rozier (CHA) retreats alongside Beal's (WAS) path and marginal body contact occurs at the end of Beal's drive.
Avdija (WAS) engages and disengages with Bridges (CHA) as Bridges rolls toward the lane.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) brings his hand towards Ball's (CHA) arm and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Rozier (CHA) brings a hand and forearm toward Beal's (WAS) path and marginal contact occurs to Beal's front as he drives into the lane.
Martin (CHA) does not establish a legal guarding position outside of the RA prior to contact occurring with Beal (WAS) during the driving shot attempt.
Avdija (WAS) engages and disengages with Ball (CHA) during the inbound.
Gafford (WAS) and Plumlee (CHA) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Plumlee (CHA) establishes himself in a screening position in Caldwell-Pope's (WAS) path and does not deliver the contact as the switch takes place.
Avdija (WAS) jumps to the side of Rozier (CHA) and legally contests his jump shot attempt.
Gafford (WAS) and Plumlee (CHA) jump toward one another in pursuit of the rebound and incidental body contact occurs.
Plumlee (CHA) attempts to commit a take foul on Gafford (WAS) and the contact is marginal.
Ball (CHA) commits a take foul on Beal (WAS).
Ball (CHA) brings his off-arm toward Avdija's (WAS) front and marginal contact occurs as Ball releases away from the oncoming pick.
Plumlee (CHA) firms up in his screening position in Avdija's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact.
Ball (CHA) gathers the ball in both hands and resumes his dribble.
Avijda (WAS) and Plumlee (CHA) engage and disengage with one another in the lane during rebounding.
Rozier (CHA) commits a take foul on Kuzma (WAS).
Plumlee (CHA) and Gafford (WAS) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Kuzma (WAS) places his hand momentarily on Plumlee's (CHA) upper half and quickly slides it off.
Kuzma (WAS) and Avdija (WAS) legally contest Hayward's (CHA) jump shot attempt.
Plumlee (CHA) extends his left arm outward and marginal contact occurs with Gafford (WAS) as Gafford jumps toward the corner.
Bridges (CHA) commits a take foul on Bertans (WAS).
Plumlee (CHA) makes clean contact with the ball and ties Beal (WAS) up in the corner. A jump ball is correctly assessed.
Bridges (CHA) commits a take foul on Gafford (WAS).

Gafford (WAS) is moving forward toward Rozier (CHA) and marginal body contact occurs after Rozier receives the inbound pass. Gafford and Rozier then make incidental foot-to-foot contact with one another.
